  (b) infringe intellectual-property rights, circumvent technical protection
      measures in violation of applicable law, or breach a license or contract
      that governs the input you provide to the Software;

  (c) violate any applicable law, regulation, or export control; or

  (d) develop, stage, or distribute malicious software, or otherwise cause
      harm to systems, data, or persons.

Because the Software extracts and executes external system binaries against
adversarial input, run it only in an environment you are authorized to use and
that is appropriately isolated for the analysis of untrusted content.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. SECURITY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Software processes untrusted input by design. Although it implements
defensive controls (argv-only subprocess execution with no shell
interpolation, per-extractor timeouts, bounded output capture, path-traversal
auditing with quarantine, and byte and file-count quotas), no software can
guarantee complete safety when handling adversarial artifacts.

You are responsible for operating the Software in a suitably hardened and
isolated environment (for example, a disposable analysis virtual machine or
container without access to sensitive networks or data). Extracted content may
itself be malicious; you are responsible for handling, storing, and disposing
of extracted artifacts securely.

Security vulnerabilities in the Software should be reported privately in
accordance with the project's SECURITY.md rather than via public issues.

